Expressions are building block of programs. Computes a value from a number of operands.

int length = 20; //expressions. literal integer used to initialize variable
int width = 40;
int area = length*width; //multiplication

length = 99;

Distinguish between length on left-hand side of an assignment or iniitialization 
(the lvalue of length o rthe object named length) and legngth used on right hand side 
of assignme dor initialization (the rvalue of length, the value of the object named length).

As lvalue - length refers to box (object). As rvalue, length refers to value of box. 
